import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react'; import { useParams, useNavigate } from 'react-router-dom'; import './PlaceDetail.css'; const PlaceDetail = () => { const { placeId } = useParams(); const navigate = useNavigate(); const [place, setPlace] = useState(null); const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true); useEffect(() => { // Mock place data - in a real app, this would fetch from your backend const mockPlace = { id: placeId, name: 'Mount Cinder Viewpoint', location: 'Cascade Mountains, OR', description: 'Mount Cinder Viewpoint offers breathtaking panoramic views of the entire Cascade Mountain range, including the iconic peaks of Mount Hood and Mount Jefferson. It\'s a prime location for photography, bird watching, and enjoying serene sunsets. The well-maintained trail to the viewpoint is accessible for most skill levels, making it a popular spot for both casual visitors and avid hikers. The area here is crisp and clean, providing a refreshing escape from city life. Visitors often bring picnics to enjoy the natural beauty.', image: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1506905925346-21bda4d32df4?w=800&h=400&fit=crop', rating: 4.7, reviews: 53, openingHours: { monday: '6:00 AM - 6:00 PM', tuesday: '6:00 AM - 6:00 PM', wednesday: '6:00 AM - 6:00 PM', thursday: '6:00 AM - 6:00 PM', friday: '9:00 AM - 8:00 PM', saturday: '8:00 AM - 8:00 PM', sunday: '8:00 AM - 6:00 PM' }, contact: { address: '2500 Viewpoint Rd, Cascade Mountains, OR 97000', phone: '(555) 123-4567', website: 'mountcinderviewpoint.org' }, features: ['Pet-friendly', 'Scenic Views', 'Hiking Trails', 'Picnic Areas', 'Wildlife Spotting'], userReviews: [ { id: 1, author: 'Alex Johnson', date: 'April 15, 2024', rating: 5, comment: 'Absolutely stunning views! The hike was moderately challenging but completely worth it for the panoramic reward. Highly recommend visiting at sunset for incredible photo opportunities.' }, { id: 2, author: 'Maria Rodriguez', date: 'April 10, 2024', rating: 4, comment: 'A beautiful spot for a day trip. The facilities were clean, and the trails were well-marked. Lost one star because it can get quite crowded on weekends, but still a fantastic experience.' }, { id: 3, author: 'David Lee', date: 'March 28, 2024', rating: 5, comment: 'Came here for a picnic with the family, and it was perfect! The kids loved exploring, and the views were incredible. Very peaceful during the weekdays.' } ] }; setPlace(mockPlace); setLoading(false); }, [placeId]); if (loading) { return
Loading place details...
